{
  "texts": [
    "Evidence gathering could help recalibrate obligations to avoid excessive burdens stifling market dynamism and growth.",
    "Targeted financial support for compliance may also be warranted.",
    "PsThe most substantial impacts of the DSA will be felt by major online platforms qualifying as VLOPs and VLOSEs.",
    "These are intermediaries reaching the threshold of having an active EU user base equivalent to over 10% of the EU's population, set at around 45 million monthly active users.VLOPs like Google, Facebook, Instagram, X, TikTok and YouTube will have to comply with extensive transparency requirements, risk assessment obligations, independent auditing duties, and enhanced due diligence expectations under the DSA [51].For transparency, VLOPs will need to provide researchers access to platform data to enable continuous monitoring of risks and research in the public interest.",
    "Their annual transparency reports must contain extensive details on content moderation activities, algorithmic systems, and ad targeting.VLOPs will also have to conduct and publish annual risk assessments evaluating potential harms to electoral processes, public security, civic discourse, user rights, and equality emerging from their services' design, algorithms and policies."
  ]
}